column7:
PSA is looking to appoint a native Arabic speaking Analyst to support its growing Middle East practice. Based in Beirut, the Analyst is primarily responsible for supporting the overall due diligence process. 

 Key responsibilities include: 

 Support the preparation of Enhanced Due Diligence reports by conducting Arabic and English internet media searches to provide biographical background information on individuals / entities within the public domain; 
 Identify and approach potential sources (telephone or in person interviews) for purposes of conducting reputational inquiries on companies and their associated key executives. 
 Coordinate with local in-country sources during report preparation to ensure completeness of reporting; 
 Edit due diligence reports for consistency and accuracy of findings; 
 Take on additional responsibilities as required to support the due diligence case management. 

 Education & Experience: University degree in with at least 2-3 years of relevant experience is required; research experience in consulting or journalism is preferable 

 Language Requirements: Excellent English and Arabic language skills. Knowledge of French is an advantage.  
 Applicants may send a resume and a brief cover letter to recruitment@psagroup.com

