Center for Corporate Services (CCS) is a leading provider of specialized training services, financial advisory services and management consultancy services, based in Lebanon, and serving the entire GCC and the wider MENA regions. 

Our services cover a wide variety of individuals, institutions as well as intergovernmental organizations. 

We are distinguished from others by our deep industry and sector knowledge and expertise including but not limited to: 
• Banking;
• Telecommunication;
• Manufacturing;
• Insurance; 
• Oil and Gas;
• Food And Beverage; and
• Real Estate.

We collaborate with our customers in all sectors and regions to identify their highest-value opportunities, address their most critical challenges and add value to their businesses.

Our customized and tailor made approach ensures that our customers:
• Achieve endurable competitive advantage;
• Build more proficient organizations; and
• Secure long-lasting objectives.

We have brought together a highly skilled team of trainers, advisors and consultants with diverse educational backgrounds and professional experience capable of quality execution by continuously exceeding our customers’ expectations.

column7:
We are seeking an operations administrator to become part of our dynamic team in Beirut.     Required General Skills and Qualifications: 

Language: A good level of written and spoken Arabic and English is essential.

Education: A bachelor’s degree. 

Computer skills: Experience and competency with basic programs is essential (Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook). Experience with intellectual property software is an advantage.

Experience: 1-2 years.  
   Responsibilities:

The role of Operations Administrator includes carrying out the following functions:

• Scanning, filing and profiling of documents and correspondences;
• Maintaining filing and storage systems;
• Preparing applications to submit to Government Ministries; 
• Attending to post office and various formalities at Government Ministries including legalisation and notarisation of documents;
• Handling courier, sorting incoming and outgoing mail together with distribution of operations post and providing administrative assistance when required;
• Attending to the entry and update of IP portfolio data;
• Managing trade mark journals, processing and checking IP advertisements/publications and assisting in IP certificates related work; and 
• Managing and auditing formalities documents.
